Our group is in charge of composing
the main theme song for this drama.

75
00:04:36,709 --> 00:04:41,781
My kid is asleep at night so I needed to
figure out where I could play instruments.

76
00:04:41,848 --> 00:04:45,018
But I found some time
and composed up to the chorus for now.

77
00:04:45,084 --> 00:04:48,388
But since then, I haven't had
much time to play any instruments.

78
00:04:49,622 --> 00:04:51,624
What time do we start again?

79
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:55,194
<i>There's one thing
that supports him during these busy days.</i>

80
00:04:55,261 --> 00:04:59,465
<i>Those are the memories of his mother
raising him with all her heart.</i>

81
00:05:04,737 --> 00:05:07,540
<i>During a drama promotion interview...</i>

82
00:05:11,577 --> 00:05:18,217
My mother is very old-fashioned,
very Showa period.

83
00:05:18,284 --> 00:05:20,586
She's the stereotypical mother from Osaka.

84
00:05:20,653 --> 00:05:25,425
My mother would always say,
"That's such a waste."

85
00:05:25,491 --> 00:05:27,894
There's a river called Yamato River.

86
00:05:28,728 --> 00:05:32,965
I caught two carp one time
when I was in elementary school.

87
00:05:33,032 --> 00:05:36,502
I told her, "I got two of them!"
"That's wonderful," she would reply.

88
00:05:36,569 --> 00:05:39,672
I put them in the water tank
in the back somewhere.

89
00:05:39,739 --> 00:05:43,042
That night, we had grilled fish.

90
00:05:43,743 --> 00:05:47,213
When I said, "My fish!"
She replied, "I grilled them."

91
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:48,781
"Just eat them," she said.

92
00:05:48,848 --> 00:05:52,085
The next day, I came home
and I said, "I'm hungry."

93
00:05:52,151 --> 00:05:55,188
I look over and she says,
"I boiled them in soy sauce today."

94
00:05:56,556 --> 00:06:01,127
Can you please place your legs
in the pink area? Thank you.

95
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:02,261
Here I go.

96
00:06:02,328 --> 00:06:06,566
<i>Joshima did not have
an easy time as a young boy,</i>

97
00:06:06,632 --> 00:06:09,302
<i>but he decided to become a pop idol.</i>

98
00:06:09,369 --> 00:06:10,536
Okay.

99
00:06:10,603 --> 00:06:12,905
FULL OF LOVE

100
00:06:15,041 --> 00:06:20,246
{\an8}<i>In 1990, when the three formed TOKIO,</i>

101
00:06:20,313 --> 00:06:22,749
{\an8}<i>Joshima was already 19 years old.</i>

102
00:06:24,217 --> 00:06:28,221
<i>He was oldest and the leader of the group.</i>

103
00:06:28,287 --> 00:06:29,822
UNDERSTAND THE EFFORT WE MAKE!

104
00:06:29,889 --> 00:06:34,260
<i>Joshima wanted to change his life.</i>

105
00:06:36,095 --> 00:06:38,865
I saw Shonentai on TV,

106
00:06:39,832 --> 00:06:43,736
they were in the spotlight,
singing and dancing.

107
00:06:43,803 --> 00:06:46,072
"I can't believe
there's a world like this."

108
00:06:46,139 --> 00:06:50,209
If I jump into that spotlight,
my life will change.

109
00:06:50,777 --> 00:06:56,215
I wanted to free myself
from everyday life.

110
00:06:56,282 --> 00:06:58,117
I wanted to change.

111
00:06:58,184 --> 00:07:02,021
I didn't belong anywhere,
so I wanted to jump into that spotlight.

112
00:07:02,088 --> 00:07:07,326
I have memories
of feeling like that back then.

113
00:07:09,662 --> 00:07:15,268
<i>However, 19 years old
is a slow start for a pop idol.</i>

114
00:07:16,402 --> 00:07:19,772
<i>He had one weapon though.</i>

115
00:07:23,109 --> 00:07:25,645
<i>That was the guitar.</i>

116
00:07:42,228 --> 00:07:44,263
Makes me want to drink tea from a teacup.

117
00:07:46,265 --> 00:07:48,267
Back home in high school,

118
00:07:48,334 --> 00:07:51,337
I was already playing the guitar
and forming bands.

119
00:07:51,404 --> 00:07:53,406
I thought I'd go for what I'm good at.

120
00:07:53,473 --> 00:07:55,475
I used to play at the dorms.

121
00:07:55,541 --> 00:07:57,543
Mr. Johnny saw me and said,

122
00:07:57,610 --> 00:08:01,314
"If you like instruments so much,
why don't you form a band?"

123
00:08:01,948 --> 00:08:05,685
And that's how TOKIO started.

124
00:08:07,687 --> 00:08:10,957
<i>They were a rare type of an idol group.</i>

125
00:08:11,023 --> 00:08:13,926
<i>TOKIO was born as a rock band.</i>

126
00:08:16,963 --> 00:08:20,166
<i>Sometimes they would wear
T-shirts or nothing at all.</i>

127
00:08:20,233 --> 00:08:22,935
<i>They've always done things their own way.</i>

128
