the first part one more time?

218
00:13:26,005 --> 00:13:32,912
<i>There, Joshima had his own thoughts
after being TOKIO's leader for many years.</i>

219
00:13:35,648 --> 00:13:39,385
Everyone has their own way
of singing, acting, and living.

220
00:13:39,451 --> 00:13:42,488
Their habits show
in their personality too.

221
00:13:42,555 --> 00:13:44,156
Even if something feels missing,

222
00:13:44,223 --> 00:13:46,525
there are times
when that's completely okay.

223
00:13:46,592 --> 00:13:49,528
And there are times
when something's missing a tiny piece

224
00:13:49,595 --> 00:13:52,198
and if we had it,
we would complete the puzzle.

225
00:13:52,264 --> 00:13:54,466
But it's just that
one piece that's missing.

226
00:13:54,533 --> 00:13:58,504
Like if it were a building,
even without that piece,

227
00:13:58,571 --> 00:14:00,306
it won't fall down when it shakes.

228
00:14:00,372 --> 00:14:02,441
I don't like things to be too perfect.

229
00:14:02,508 --> 00:14:07,379
And I don't think any of us
in TOKIO are perfect.

230
00:14:07,446 --> 00:14:09,481
But because of
the imperfections, the gaps,

231
00:14:09,548 --> 00:14:12,985
we've been able to do well
and succeed in our endeavors.

232
00:14:13,052 --> 00:14:16,455
And this would make me question
if there is a right way to do things.

233
00:14:17,957 --> 00:14:20,426
<i>They don't try to fit
into a certain shape.</i>

234
00:14:23,729 --> 00:14:26,866
{\an8}I think the Johnny's Shop
was established in 1988.

